{{Infobox criminal | name = Brian J. Doyle | image_name = Brian Doyle.jpg | image_size = 150px | image_caption = mug shot of Doyle | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|04|07|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[United States]] | death_date = | death_place = | alias = | conviction = attempt solicitation of a child for sex | conviction_penalty = imprisonment of five years, probation of ten years | conviction_status = incarcerated at [[Wakulla Correctional Institution]] Annex | occupation = former Deputy [[Press secretary|Press Secretary]] | spouse = | parents = | children = }}
'''Brian James Doyle''' (born April 7, 1950) is a former Deputy Press Secretary in the [[United States Department of Homeland Security]]. In 2006, he was indicted for seducing a 14-year-old girl, who was actually a sheriff's deputy working undercover, on the internet. He was arrested on April 4, 2006, at his home in [[Silver Spring, Maryland]].<ref>{{cite news|publisher=[[CNN]]|url=http://www.cnn.com/2006/LAW/04/04/homeland.arrest/index.html|title=Homeland Security official arrested in child sex sting|date=April 5, 2006}}</ref> Five months later, he [[plea|pled]] [[Nolo contendere|no contest]]. On November 17, 2006, he was sentenced to five years in [[prison]], with ten years of [[probation]], and he was registered as a [[sex offender]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theledger.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20061118/NEWS/611180430/1039|title=Ex-Homeland Security Employee 5 Years in Prison for Porn E-mails|first=Dana|last=Willhoit|date=November 18, 2006|publisher=[[The Ledger]]}}</ref> Doyle was incarcerated at Wakulla Correctional Institution Annex outside of Tallahassee, Florida. He was released from prison on January 15, 2011.<ref name="DOC">{{cite web |url=http://www.dc.state.fl.us/ActiveInmates/inmateaction.asp?DataAction=GetInmate&DCNumber=H25603 |title=Inmate Population Information Detail - Brian J. Doyle |publisher=[[Florida Department of Corrections]] |accessdate=February 4, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605041851/http://www.dc.state.fl.us/ActiveInmates/inmateaction.asp?DataAction=GetInmate&DCNumber=H25603 |archivedate=June 5, 2011 |df= }}</ref>{{failed verification|date=November 2012}}
