{{Infobox Artwork | image_file = Odd Nerdrum Frigjoering.jpg | title = Liberation | artist = [[Odd Nerdrum]] | year = 1974 | medium = [[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric = 202 | width_metric = 283 | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = | city = | museum = Private collection }} '''''Liberation''''' ({{Lang-no|'''Frigjøring'''}}) is a 1974 painting by the Norwegian artist [[Odd Nerdrum]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.artprice.com/marketplace/1214457/odd-nerdrum/painting/liberation|title=Odd Nerdrum – Liberation|work=Artprice.com|accessdate=2016-09-26}}</ref> It depicts a room with a mattress where a couple have sexual intercourse with the [[woman on top]] of the passive man.
Nerdrum's art from the period 1968–1983 is characterized by everyday [[Realism (arts)|realism]] and left-wing politics.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Blom|first1=Hege|last2=Reisegg|first2=Øyvind|url=https://snl.no/Odd%20Nerdrum|title=Odd Nerdrum|language=Norwegian|work=[[Store norske leksikon]]|accessdate=2016-09-26}}</ref> ''Liberation'' was created in this context, where the radical left propounded a [[sexual revolution]] as a way to create a [[socialism|socialist]] utopia by politicizing every aspect of human life, especially sexuality. Nerdrum made several paintings on the topic of what was considered sexual liberation. The most famous of these are ''Liberation'' from 1974 and ''Spring'' (''Vår'') from 1977.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Ebbestad Hansen|first=Jan-Erik|year=1996|title=Fenomenet Nerdrum|language=Norwegian|location=Oslo|publisher=[[Gyldendal Norsk Forlag]]|page=83|isbn=82-05-24492-8}}</ref>
==Provenance== The painting was first presented at [[Høstutstillingen]] in 1974. It was exhibited at the Oslo gallery Kunstnerforbundet in 1976 as part of the exhibition Odd Nerdrum Malerier ("Odd Nerdrum Paintings").<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.blomqvist.no/Kunsthandel/Moderne-contemporary-og-eldre-kunst/Nerdrum-Odd-Frigjoering-1974|title=Nerdrum, Odd - Frigjøring 1974|language=Norwegian|publisher=Blomqvist Kunsthandel|accessdate=2016-09-26}}</ref>
