{{Infobox language |name=Nguluwan |states=[[Federated States of Micronesia]] |region=[[Ngulu Atoll]] |speakers=50 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Admiralty Island languages|Admiralty Islands]] ? |fam5=[[Yapese language|Yapese]] |iso3=nuw |glotto=ngul1236 |glottorefname=Nguluwan }}
'''Nguluwan''' is a [[mixed language]] spoken on an atoll of that name between [[Yap]] and [[Palau]]. The grammar and lexicon are [[Yapese language|Yapese]], but the phonology has been affected by [[Ulithian language|Ulithian]], and speakers are shifting to that language.
