{{Infobox language |name=Sebat Bet Gurage |nativename= |pronunciation= |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region= West [[Gurage Zone]] |speakers= 440,000 |date=no date |ref=e15 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Semitic languages|Semitic]] |fam3=[[South Semitic languages|South]] |fam4=[[Ethiopian Semitic languages|Ethiopian]] |fam5=South |fam6=Outer |fam7=[[West Gurage languages|West Gurage]] |iso3=sgw |glotto=seba1251 |glottorefname=Sebat Bet Gurage |script=Ethiopic }}
'''Sebat Bet''' ("Seven houses") is an [[Afroasiatic languages|Afroasiatic language]] spoken in [[Ethiopia]].
==Overview== One of the [[Gurage languages]], Sebat Bet is divided into several dialects. The latter are spoken in the western [[Gurage Zone]]: *[[Chaha language|Chaha]] (Cheha) is spoken in [[Cheha]] and is the best studied of these varieties *[[Ezha language|Ezha]] (Eza, Izha) is spoken in [[Ezhana Wolene]] *[[Muher language|Muher]] is spoken in the mountains north of Cheha and Ezhaha Wolene *[[Gura language|Gura]] is spoken in [[Goro, SNNPR (woreda)|Goro woreda]] *[[Gumer language|Gumer]] (Gwemarra, Gʷəmarə), spoken in [[Gumer]] *[[Inor language|Inor]] (Enemor), spoken in [[Enemorina Eaner]] :*[[Gyeto language|Gyeto]], [[Endegegn language|Endegegn]] and the extinct [[Mesmes language]] are sometimes considered subdialects of Inor.
==Notes== {{Reflist}}
